June 17 (Reuters) - The COVAX facility, backed by the World Health Organization (WHO) and the Global Alliance for Vaccines and Immunization (GAVI), has delivered 1.53 billion COVID-19 vaccine doses to 146 countries, GAVI data shows. In December, COVAX set a target of achieving 70% COVID-19 immunization coverage by mid-2022. The following tables list countries that have received vaccines under the scheme in alphabetic order: AFRICA & MIDDLE EAST EUROPE ASIA & PACIFIC AMERICAS Sources: WHO, UNICEF, GAVI, releases from local authorities Our Standards: The Thomson Reuters Trust Principles.